COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 541, L.D. 1311
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment clarifies that the Maine Health Care Education Training and Medical
33 Residency Fund may be used for clinical preceptorships and clinical rotations for all health
44 profession students in rural and underserved communities. It also provides that the fund
55 may be used to expand rural residency positions and rotations for medical school graduates
66 in the State, instead of medical students as in the bill. It reduces the funding required for
77 the fund from $5,000,000 to $1,950,000 per fiscal year.
